Basic Syntax
sequence[start:stop:step]

•	start: Index to begin the slice (inclusive). Defaults to 0 if omitted.
•	stop: Index to end the slice (exclusive). Defaults to the length of the sequence if omitted.
•	step: Interval between elements. Defaults to 1 if omitted.
Examples
a = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70]

print(a[1:4])      # [20, 30, 40]
print(a[:3])       # [10, 20, 30]
print(a[::2])      # [10, 30, 50, 70]
print(a[::-1])     # [70, 60, 50, 40, 30, 20, 10] (reversed list)

Why Use Slicing?
•	Extract sublists or substrings
•	Reverse sequences
•	Skip elements with a step
•	Efficiently manipulate data without loops

You can even use the built-in slice() function to create slice objects dynamically:
s = slice(1, 5, 2)
print(a[s])  # [20, 40]
